{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Size}}
__TOC__

== Description ==
R<b>'Size</b> is a [[:Category:Ada Programming/Representation attributes|representation attribute]] used to get the number of bits of an object or type:
* When applied to an object, 'Size yields the actual number of bits allocated to store the object. 
* When applied to types, 'Size yields the ''minimum'' number of bits required to store an object of that type. 

Thus, the 'Size of a type might be lower than the 'Size of its objects. This is especially important to note for '''[[Ada Programming/Types/record#Variant_record|variant records]]''', where a particular instance of the record may be much larger than the smallest possible record instance.

The 'Size attribute may also be used to set the minimum size in bits used to store a type.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/Sourceforge|attributes_size.adb}}

 {{Ada/kw|with}} {{Ada/package|Ada|Text_IO}};

 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Attributes_Size {{Ada/kw|is}}

    {{Ada/kw|package}} T_IO {{Ada/kw|renames}} Ada.Text_IO;
    {{Ada/kw|package}} I_IO {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|new}}  Ada.Text_IO.Integer_IO (Integer);

    A_Boolean : {{Ada/kw|constant}} Boolean := True;
 {{Ada/kw|begin}}
    T_IO.Put ("Size of Boolean type   = "); {{Ada/--|An enumeration with}}
    I_IO.Put (Boolean'Size);                {{Ada/--|2 values fits into}}
    T_IO.New_Line;                          {{Ada/--|1 bit.}}

    T_IO.Put ("Size of Boolean Object = "); {{Ada/--|it is more efficient}}
    I_IO.Put (A_Boolean'Size);              {{Ada/--|to store a boolean}}
    T_IO.New_Line;                          {{Ada/--|as an entire byte}}
 {{Ada/kw|end}} Attributes_Size;

The output with GNAT 3.4.1 will be:

 Size of Boolean type   =           1
 Size of Boolean Object =           8

Try it yourself and see how your compiler does.

== Incorrect usages ==

{{:Ada Programming/Attributes/'Size:3}}

